(267, 127, '_wp_page_template', 'page-about.php'),
(269, 127, 'title', 'Our Story'),
(270, 127, '_title', 'field_624230b6c526b'),
(271, 127, 'content', 'Our toddler was finally going back to daycare after spending a year at home during COVID. It was going to be a big adjustment, and I wanted to prepare him as best I could. So I wrote \"his back-to-school story\" with pictures of home and of his new school. We read the book for several weeks leading up to his first day. And soon our little one was able to tell us his story of going back to school!  The transition was as smooth as we could have hoped for.\r\n\r\nI kept writing books - about arrival of a baby brother,  moving to a new home, being in our cousin\'s wedding, and many more. My books worked so well for my kids, that we set out to create a simple way for other parents to make<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\"> personalized photo storybooks</span> to prepare their kids for change, too.\r\n\r\nWe know your little ones will love their Up &amp; Coming books as much as our kids do, and your families will treasure these books which commemorate milestones in their life.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Best,</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Rebecca and Boris</span>'),
(272, 127, '_content', 'field_62423102c526d'),
(273, 127, 'title_build', 'Build your book now'),
(274, 127, '_title_build', 'field_62423137c526f'),
(275, 127, 'buttontext', 'Get started'),
(276, 127, '_buttontext', 'field_62423149c5270'),
(277, 127, 'buttonlink', '10'),
(278, 127, '_buttonlink', 'field_62423157c5271'),
(279, 127, 'image', '2133'),
(280, 127, '_image', 'field_62423168c5272'),
(281, 137, 'title', 'Subtitle'),
(282, 137, '_title', 'field_624230b6c526b'),
(283, 137, 'content', 'Our firstborn was still nursing for comfort at 2.5 years old, and I was pregnant with our second child. I wanted to wean before the new baby arrived, but how? I knew I’d have to prepare my older kiddo for this change if my effort was going to be successful. So I wrote him a book - his weaning story. We read the book frequently in the weeks leading up to weaning day. And by then, he was able to tell his own weaning story to us! The transition was as smooth as I could have hoped for.\r\n\r\nSince then, I’ve written many more books for our kids to help them understand and feel prepared for various life events - starting school, travel/moves, new babies in the family, etc. Even after the book has served its purpose and our kids have successfully navigated through another change, we treasure these books which also commemorate milestones in their development.\r\n\r\nMy husband Boris and I created Up &amp; Coming Books to make it easy for other families to create similar personalized photo storybooks to help kids through life’s'),
(284, 137, '_content', 'field_62423102c526d'),
